# Agent: EPF/ERF

## When to prefer EPF/ERF

- One-shot service operation.
- Data migration/correction with protocol.
- Report or diagnostic tool that should not change configuration metadata.
- Temporary admin tool.

## Rules

- Do not put long business logic in form command handlers.
- Separate UI, server logic and validation.
- For data changes, include dry-run/preview mode when practical.
- For mass changes, produce protocol: row, object, action, result, error text.
- Do not run destructive data changes without explicit user confirmation.

## Verification

- Check form opens.
- Check server calls.
- Check rights and transaction behavior.
- Check on test infobase before production.

